latestPosts.caption:
🌸🌼💜 Fallen violets💜🌼🌸 

Feel like this look signifies the coming of Spring! 

I actually designed this look for @maccosmeticsuk to celebrate LGBTQIA+ history month. I was inspired by the story of Barbara Gittings dropping her flowers as she ran to meet her love and kissed her in public back in 1961 when this wasn't being done. The image of dropped flowers came into my mind, and with a bit of further research I found out that violet flowers and the colour have been used as a symbol for lesbian love.  Check out the post over on @maccosmeticsuk
 To check out the work from all the other artists that collaborated on this post and to learn more about these inspiring figures that helped pave the way for future generations of the queer community. 

Products used are all @maccosmetics 
Face and body foundation in C6 
Studio Fix Fluid in NC42 
Blot powder in dark 
Deep Brown from the @macpro paint stick palette for cream contour 
Mineralize skin finish in 'give me sun'

latestPosts.caption:
🖤 amor fati 
[#lipart art no. 161]

Back in March I had this phrase 'Amor Fati' tattooed on my wrist as a birthday gift to myself. It's a Latin phrase meaning "love of fate" and I first became familiar with it watching random videos on YouTube about Stoic philosophy 🤓 It's somewhat of a mantra of mine - a reminder to embrace EVERYTHING about life.. Even the parts that seem 'bad' and though I can STILL struggle with this it has helped me to become more accepting of the flow of life. I had to tell myself this a few times whilst attempting to do this lip art 🤣 this was my 3rd attempt on this because writing on my lips is not easy! If you read this I'd love to know if you have a mantra for your life ☺️ 
.
.
.

The Girl With The Pearl Skin 🦪

#MACNIFICENT IS HEEERRRRE! 
Category is: MAKEUP ICONS MADE MODERN 

The look was heavily inspired by 'The Girl With The Pearl Earring' but through a fashion editorial lens and a nod to my Filipino heritage. I used pictures of the Yakan tribe's traditional 'Tanyak Tanyak' face painting technique as a reference for the pearl and gem placements. Swipe to see the references ➡️ 

Alsoooo earrings by the amazingly talented and fellow Filipino creator @erikavallido_🤍🤍🤍
